  sodium: 4.4 g
  serving size: 351
servings: 2
---

Bring a large pan of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the noodles.

Trim the @pak choi{1} then thinly slice widthways.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Zest and halve the @lime{0.5}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} over medium high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper and stir fry until slightly softened and starting to colour, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes} then drain in a #colander{} and run under cold water to prevent the noodles from sticking. Set aside.

Add the @king prawns{150%g} and bok choy to the pan with the pepper and stir fry until the prawns are almost cooked, ~{3%minutes}.

Add the garlic to the prawns and stir fry until the prawns are cooked, ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the @hoisin sauce{50%ml}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @sugar{0.5%tsp} and a splash of @water{} along with the lime zest.

Bring the sauce to a simmer then add the noodles and mix through the sauce.

Cook until everything is piping hot, ~{1%minute}. Add a squeeze of lime juice.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs loosening up.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges.

Divide the stir fry between your plates and serve with the lime wedges. Enjoy!